The Chairman of the House of Representatives Committee on Navy and top aspirant for the speakership seat of the House of Representatives, Hon. Yusuf Gagdi has congratulated the Speaker, Hon. Femi Gbajabiamila and Senator George Akume on their appointments as Chief Of Staff to President Bola Tinubu and Secretary To Government Of The Federation, SGF respectively. Gagdi in a statement said he was elated by the choice of the Speaker because he has no reservation about his competence and ability to support President Tinubu to achieve his lofty plans for the growth and development of Nigeria. He added that as a seasoned Lawmaker that has well over 20 years of experience in the workings of the Legislature, he is confident that Gbajabiamila will work to create a productive relationship between the two arms of government that will ultimately benefit the Nigerian people. He also applauded the appointment of Senator George Akume as the Secretary to the Government of the Federation (SGF) and former Deputy Governor of Jigawa, Ibrahim Hadejia, as Deputy Chief of Staff. According to the Lawmaker, the persons appointed demonstrate President Tinubuâ€™s resolve to appoint only competent persons that can perform optimally for the overall good of the country. In his prayer, Gagdi asked the Almighty God to grant them wisdom to discharge their duties effectively.